
*** HOW TO USE TRON LIBS (DADY PROGRAM)


> INTRODUCTION

dady is a program that allows users to control robotic nodes (amy, goon, willy, ...) through CLI.

It uses tron libraries:
- libtron_talky for robotic language interpretation.
- libtron_comy for IPC communication.
- libtron_tuly for utilities.


> USAGE

usage: dady <talky message>

note: use dady without params to get the list of topics, categories and concepts available for communication.


> INSTALLATION


1. Install tron libs

follow instructions in file howto_install_tron


2. Build dady project (in Netbeans)

3. Create link to dady executable:
 
cd <desired_folder>
ln -s <tron_installation_path>/dady/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux/dady dady



